    "body": "The work after poll (reading a message, getting control back to the\napplication) can quickly become dominated by context switches if there are\ntoo many threads involved in processing in the response path (especially if\nyour network is fast), so we try to design so that there's a minimum number\nof thread jumps involved in any path.\n\nOn Tue, Sep 13, 2016 at 11:34 PM 武苍石 notifications@github.com wrote:\n\n> in ev_poll_posix.c:pollset_work function, multiple thread can block in\n> poll？\n> why design so that？why not make a thread to do poll。\n> \n> —\n> You are receiving this because you are subscribed to this thread.\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/8091, or mute the thread\n> https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AJpudQN8XynmJqxGro3Ghc-u8h766rIrks5qp5VggaJpZM4J8cXa\n> .\n"
